		<div id="comment_body_65026283"><p>As a cybersecurity expert, I disagree.</p><p>Humans have a lot of inertia and they fight change constantly.</p><p>Sometimes, they need to be forced to adopt new things for their own good.</p><p>Passkeys are not only more secure, but they are better for everyone because you no longer need to remember passwords. They are so, so much better. But if we relied on users to adopt them at-will, then we would be waiting a decade - a decade where we'd have to continue to be funding terrorist networks with the proceeds of cybercrime.</p></div>
	</div>

