		<div class="title">
			<h4><a rel="nofollow" id="comment_link_65026517" name="comment_link_65026517" href="//it.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23556325&amp;cid=65026517" onclick="return D2.setFocusComment(65026517)" >Re: Passkeys are better for everyone</a>


		 	<span id="comment_score_65026517" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 65026517); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>2</a>)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~Viol8">Viol8</a>  <span class="uid"><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~Viol8">( 599362 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_65026517"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65026517"><p>And if I want to log into something from a 3rd party machine? Load the passkey on to it [somehow] then make sure I delete it again after [somehow]. Fuck that. A login and password takes seconds even with a 2fa sms.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_65026517">

